-- MOVES-BofA Merrill Lynch makes four appointments to GTS, EMEA team
-- By Lehar Maan in Bengaluru
-- Wed Dec 17, 2014 08:31AM EST
-- None



Dec 17 (Reuters) - Bank of America Merrill Lynch made four appointments in its global transaction services (GTS), EMEA team.

The bank named Peter Jameson head of trade. In this role, Jameson will lead the trade team to create working capital solutions for multinational, middle-market and FI clients. He will remain co-head of product management, GTS EMEA. BofA Merrill Lynch also appointed Matthew Davies, who will work alongside Jameson, as co-head of product management.